result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court calls @ 4:15 PM/ RM 203, 22CF156 & 22CF193. Defendant Anna M. Ramos-Golden appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail. Attorney Elizabeth R. Gebert in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. Court reviews case history's. Def. has Atty. Anne Katte on 22CF156. Def. has applied and is eligible for PD in 22CF193 and Court notes appointment of counsel report. Def. is okay to proceed with P.H. today. State is ready to proceed with P.H., has been in contact with Def. Attorney Anne Katte and notes Def. understands there can only be one P.H. with our without counsel. State requests Court find transactional relationship among the charges that are filed in the criminal complaint. Court reviews complaint and finds transactional relationship among the charges that are filed in the criminal complaint. State calls first witness, Deputy Travis Krueger. Deputy Krueger sworn in under oath and testifies. Def. has no questions for witness. State rests. Court finds probable cause and binds over for further proceedings. State requests to set for arraignment at a later date. State requests 22CF156 track along as a status conference. Court notes 22CF156 will track along as status. State has complied with victims rights.
Arraignment scheduled for December 5, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court calls @ 2:45 PM/ RM 301, 22CF193 & 22CF156. Defendant Anna M. Ramos-Golden appeared by video, in custody in Langlade County Jail.  Attorney Kelly Hays in court for State of Wisconsin, via zoom. In case 22CF156 Def. has Atty Anne Katte, matter was scheduled for a status conference and will track along with 22CF193. In 22CF193, Def. has copy of complaint, advised of charges and penalties.  Def. given Atty rights and given 4 options, PD, hire own, court appointed Atty. or represent self. Def. does wish to attain counsel. Defendant to apply with Public Defender within 7 days at 715-536-9105. State notes victim not referred and State is in compliance with victim rights. State gives bail bond recommendations and requests $500,000.00 cash bond with conditions of No illegal use or possession of controlled substances and No contact with the victim. Def. has no objection. Court orders $500,000.00 cash bond with conditions of No illegal use or possession of controlled substances, No contact with the victim and Defendant to apply with Public Defender within 7 days at 715-536-9105. Court questions if Def. would like to waive time limits for P.H. and wait for counsel. Def. would like to continue with P.H. within time limits.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 25, 2022 at 04:15 pm.
